{"lemma":"صَنَمِ","slug":"صَنَمِ","root":"ص.ن.م","root_slug":"ص-ن-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ن-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25041","n25042"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"idol"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make an idol"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to represent (something) in the image of an idol"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape, to form","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become bad (of a smell)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smell bad (of the body, etc.)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Akkadian 𒀩 (ṣalmum) and Biblical Hebrew צֶלֶם (ṣɛ́lɛm), with dissimilation of /l/ to /n/.\n\nDenominal from صَنَم (ṣanam, “idol”)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.nam/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25041","headword_ar":"صنّم","root":"Snm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoniymN","text_ar":"تَصْنِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saw~ara","text_ar":"صَوَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He formed, fashioned, figured, shaped, sculptured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pictured:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. from the noun here following]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25042","headword_ar":"صَنَمٌ","root":"Snm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An idol:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an idol of a particular kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wavan","text_ar":"وَثَن"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wavan","text_ar":"وَثَن"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is worshipped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wavan","text_ar":"وَثَن"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is made of stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is said on the authority of I'Ab: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing well known, that is carved of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is made of molten and cast silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copper"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M; and the like is said in the Msb on the authority of IF:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Snm","text_ar":"صنم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of metals that melt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wvn","text_ar":"وثن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made of stone or of wood: (Msb:) or, accord. to Hishám ElKelbee, the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1736},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of other metal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, of stones: or, accord. to Ibn-'Arafeh and El-Fihree, the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an image;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter is a shapeless thing: or, as some say, the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing having corporeal from, carved of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver, and worshipped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [the latter (in the TA the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Snm","text_ar":"صنم"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this I suppose to be a mistake for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wvn","text_ar":"وثن"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] is a incorporeal form: or the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing having the form of a human being;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, a thing having some other form: or the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing having material substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shape;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, a thing not having material substance or shape: or the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other material;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, an embodied form: (TA:) or, accord. to IAth, the latter [?] is anything having corporeal form, made of metal or of wood and stones, like the form of a human being, made, and set up, and worshipped; and the former [?]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an incorporeal form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wvn","text_ar":"وثن"},{"kind":"text","text":": [from explanations given above, it seems that the reverse of this is the case:]) and Abu-l-'Abbás states, on the authority of IAar, that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanamapN","text_ar":"صَنَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSamapN","text_ar":"نَصَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an image"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwrapN","text_ar":"صُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is worshipped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.;) each of these two words is thus ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlt~aHoriyk","text_ar":"بِالتَّحْرِيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"), though it would seem that accord. to the K the latter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSomapN","text_ar":"نَصْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nSm","text_ar":"نصم"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanamN","text_ar":"صَنَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) it is said (S) is an arabicized word, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aman","text_ar":"شَمَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) [which is Pers., though SM says,] I know not in what language, for in Pers. it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bt","text_ar":"بت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buto","text_ar":"بُتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSonaAmN","text_ar":"اَصْنَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb;) which, as used in the Kur xiv. 38, is said by Er-Rághib to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things that divert one from God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}